5696	\begin{lemma}\leanok
5697	[Sq1 tail --- the R1/R5 unit collapse]
5698	  \label{lem:sheafificationcomppullback_comp_tail}
5699	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Modules.sheafificationCompPullback_comp_tail}
5700	  \uses{lem:sheafification_comp_pullback_eq_leftadjointuniq, lem:leftadjointuniq_app_unit_eta_general, lem:pullbackObjUnitToUnit_comp, lem:restrictscalarsid_map, lem:forget_map_pushforward_map}
5701	  \textit{Source: internal categorical construction; no external reference.}
5702	  After the R0-peel of \cref{lem:sheafificationcomppullback_comp}, the residual obligation is
5703	  the unit identity for the two-layer composite adjunction (presheaf pullback--pushforward
5704	  composed with sheafification). Writing \(B_\varphi\) for that sheaf-level composite
5705	  adjunction, \(\mathtt{PresheafPullback}_f\) for the presheaf-level pullback along \(f\),
5706	  \(R_1 = h^*\bigl((\mathtt{sheafCompPb}\,f).\mathrm{app}\,P\bigr)\) and
5707	  \(R_5 = (\mathtt{sheafCompPb}\,h).\mathrm{app}\,(\mathtt{PresheafPullback}_f\,P)\) for the two
5708	  sub-comparison factors, the tail asserts that the composite unit
5709	  \(B_{h \circ f}.\mathrm{unit}.\mathrm{app}\,P\) equals the sheafification-unit of \(X\)
5710	  followed by the (forgetful, change-of-rings-along-identity) image of the merged factor
5711	  \(\bigl((B_f \mathbin{.\mathrm{comp}} B_h).\mathrm{unit} \mathbin{;}
5712	  \mathtt{pushforwardComp}.\mathrm{hom}\bigr) \mathbin{;} (\text{pushforward of } R_1 \mathbin{;}
5713	  R_5 \mathbin{;} a_Z.\mathrm{map}\,\delta_{\mathrm{pre}})\).
5714	\end{lemma}
